You are viewing the BigQuery SQL script for:
-- E-Commerce Customer Segmentation (RFM Analysis) --

This repository contains the SQL transformation logic used to perform RFM (Recency, Frequency, Monetary) analysis on an e-commerce dataset containing over 541,000 transactions.

The goal of this script is to transition raw, row-level transaction data into a high-performance summary table that categorizes customers based on their purchasing behavior. 
This serves as the "Transformation" layer in a modern ELT (Extract, Load, Transform) pipeline.

--Technical
The script follows a structured multi-step process using CTLEs
Data Cleaning - Filters out null CustomerID and exludes negative Quantity or UnitPrice values.
Aggregation - Summarise the data at the CustomerID level to calculate recency(R), frequency(F), and monetary(M).
Statistical Scoring - Use the NITLE(5) window function to divide customers into quintiles 1 to 5 for each R, F, and M metric.
Behavioral Segmentation - Implements a CASE statement to map combined scores into 8 human-readable business segments (eg. Champion, Local Customer, Hibernating, At Risk).

--Tools
Platform - Google Cloud Platform
Engine - BigQuery Standard SQL
Methodology - ETL (Extract, Load, Transform)
Techniques - CTEs, Window Functions, Data Aggregation.

--Impact
The raw data is reduced from 541000 rows to app 4300 unique customer profiles
This enabling in identiying eg. the top 45% of high value customers, the target 58 "At Risk".

